{"id":"2535","name":"Log BMI","tagline":"Super simple shortcut to log your weight and/or BMI with minimal interaction","icon":"ios12 c4282601983 g59754","latest":"7622","description":"\n\t\t\t\t\t<p>This shortcut logs your BMI into Apple Health in the most efficient way possible. If Apple Health already possesses a weight entry for today, it will log your BMI without any input. If Apple Health lacks a weight entry for today, this shortcut will ask for your weight, log your weight, then log your BMI.</p>\n<p><strong>Notes</strong>: \n* Make sure your height is set in Apple Health (Medical ID tab).\n* This shortcut uses imperial measurements (feet &amp; pounds), but if there is any demand I can make a metric version.</p>\n<p><strong>Future plans</strong>\n* None yet...</p>\n\t\t\t\t","releasenotes":"<p><strong>1.1 - April 28, 2019, 7:02 p.m.</strong></p><p>Added UpdateKit support. Added feature to prevent adding multiple BMI entries per day, now limited to once per day. </p>"}